\pard\f0\fs28   Sect. CIRSIUM (Sect. {\i Chamaeleon} DC.). Leaves without rigid setae on the upper surface. Florets hermaphrodite, or the outermost functionally male or sterile. Corolla-limb 5-fid to about halfway, about as long as tube. Pappus shorter than, rarely equalling, corolla.
