\pard\f0\fs28   ({\b 30-32}). {\b C. tuberosum} group. Perennial (10-)30-80(-140) cm. Stem simple or sparingly branched, usually leafless above the middle, greyish. Leaves herbaceous, lanceolate or oblong to oblong-elliptical, patent-pubescent above and particularly on the veins beneath, also with arachnoid hairs; lobes with soft (rarely pungent) spines up to 2(-7) mm. Capitula usually solitary, long-pedunculate, rarely in clusters of 2-3, shortly pedunculate to subsessile. Involucre (14-)15-20(-25) × 11-25 mm; bracts with indistinct vittae and weak spinule. Corolla 15-25 mm, purple. Achenes 3-5 mm; pappus 13-21 mm.
\par

