\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 32. C. tuberosum} (L.) All.,{\i  Fl. Pedem.}{\b  1}: 151 (1785). Plant with short rhizome; roots with fusiform tubers. Stem with 2-3(-6) long branches or simple. Leaves sessile to semiamplexicaul, deeply pinnatifid to pinnatisect, scarcely arachnoid-hairy above, sparsely arachnoid-hairy beneath; segments with 2-3(-5) oblong to elliptic-lanceolate, dentate lobes. Capitula solitary. Involucral bracts erect; outer obtuse; middle obtuse to acute. 2n = 34.{\i  Usually in rather damp grassland; calcicole. • W. & W.C. Europe, extending to N. Italy}. †Au Br Ga Ge He Hs It *Ju [Be Cz].
