\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 34. C. montanum} (Waldst. & Kit. ex Willd.) Sprengel, {\i Syst. Veg.}{\b  3}: 376 (1826) ({\i C. tricephalodes} auct., non (Lam.) DC.). Perennial (40-)80-180(-200) cm. Stem simple or sparingly branched above, usually leafless just below apex. Leaves herbaceous, elliptical, pinnatifid, flat, subglabrous; segments narrowly triangular to oblong, dentate to shortly lobed, with weak marginal spinules up to 2 mm. Capitula in apical clusters of 2-8, rarely solitary, usually erect, sometimes exceeded by 1-3 upper leaves. Involucre 15-20 × 14-18(-21) mm; bracts with patent to deflexed apex and conspicuous vittae, with pungent spinule. Corolla 16-25 mm, purple; limb divided to halfway. Achenes 4-5·5 mm; pappus 15-22 mm. {\i Damp woods and meadows. • S. Alps, N. & C. Appennini, mountains of N. Jugoslavia.} Ga It Ju.
